   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0001",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# WP1 — Exploring Operator Corporate Websites\n",
    "\n",
    "**Research question:** How do data center operators construct and maintain the "cloud" imaginary through digital self-presentation?\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook explores the corporate website text scraped by `scripts/wp1/scrape_operator_websites.py`.\n",
    "It focuses on:\n",
    "1. Word frequency analysis — what language dominates operator self-presentation?\n",
    "2. Environmental claim language — how do operators frame sustainability?\n",
    "3. Cross-operator comparison — do different types of operator (hyperscaler vs. colocation) use different registers?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Theoretical framing:** Corporate website text is a deliberate act of framing — a form of \"cloud imaginaries\" production (cf. Mosco 2014; Holt & Vonderau 2015). The language choices are not neutral: they construct particular subject positions for operators (responsible stewards of infrastructure) and obscure others (local land use, water consumption, community impact).\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**Prerequisites:** Run the scraper first:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "python -m scripts.wp1.scrape_operator_websites \\\n",
    "    --config scripts/wp1/config_template.csv \\\n",
    "    --output data/raw/corporate-websites\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0002",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Standard library\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import re\n",
    "import csv\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "from collections import Counter\n",
    "\n",
    "# Third-party\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.ticker as mticker\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Optional NLP\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    import nltk\n",
    "    from nltk.corpus import stopwords\n",
    "    from nltk.tokenize import word_tokenize\n",
    "    for res in (\"stopwords\", \"punkt\", \"punkt_tab\"):\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            nltk.data.find(f\"tokenizers/{res}\")\n",
    "        except LookupError:\n",
    "            nltk.download(res, quiet=True)\n",
    "    STOPWORDS = set(stopwords.words(\"english\"))\n",
    "    HAVE_NLTK = True\n",
    "except ImportError:\n",
    "    HAVE_NLTK = False\n",
    "    STOPWORDS = set()\n",
    "    print(\"NLTK not installed — install with: pip install nltk\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plotting defaults\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style=\"whitegrid\", context=\"notebook\")\n",
    "plt.rcParams[\"figure.dpi\"] = 120\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Dependencies loaded.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0003",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "# Paths — adjust if you are running from a different working directory\n",
    "# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "REPO_ROOT = Path(\"../..\")  # from notebooks/wp1/ up to repo root\n",
    "CORP_DIR  = REPO_ROOT / \"data\" / \"raw\" / \"corporate-websites\"\n",
    "CONFIG    = REPO_ROOT / \"scripts\" / \"wp1\" / \"config_template.csv\"\n",
    "\n",
    "assert CORP_DIR.exists(), f\"Corporate website data not found at {CORP_DIR}. Run the scraper first.\"\n",
    "print(f\"Corporate website data directory: {CORP_DIR.resolve()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0004",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load Scraped Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Each operator subdirectory contains `.txt` files (plain text extracts) and `_meta.json` files.\n",
    "We load all available text and metadata into a flat DataFrame."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0005",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def load_operator_data(corp_dir: Path) -> pd.DataFrame:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Walk the corporate-websites directory and load all text + metadata.\"\"\"\n",
    "    records = []\n",
    "    for op_dir in sorted(corp_dir.iterdir()):\n",
    "        if not op_dir.is_dir():\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        operator_name = op_dir.name\n",
    "        for txt_file in sorted(op_dir.glob(\"*.txt\")):\n",
    "            slug = txt_file.stem\n",
    "            text = txt_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\", errors=\"replace\")\n",
    "            meta_file = op_dir / f\"{slug}_meta.json\"\n",
    "            meta = {}\n",
    "            if meta_file.exists():\n",
    "                try:\n",
    "                    meta = json.loads(meta_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n",
    "                except Exception:\n",
    "                    pass\n",
    "            records.append({\n",
    "                \"operator_name\": operator_name,\n",
    "                \"page_slug\": slug,\n",
    "                \"url\": meta.get(\"url\", \"\"),\n",
    "                \"title\": meta.get(\"title\", \"\"),\n",
    "                \"meta_description\": meta.get(\"meta_description\", \"\"),\n",
    "                \"text\": text,\n",
    "                \"text_length\": len(text),\n",
    "                \"image_alt_count\": len(meta.get(\"image_alts\", [])),\n",
    "                \"facility_link_count\": len(meta.get(\"facility_links\", [])),\n",
    "                \"keyword_counts\": meta.get(\"keyword_counts\", {}),\n",
    "            })\n",
    "    return pd.DataFrame(records)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "df = load_operator_data(CORP_DIR)\n",
    "print(f\"Loaded {len(df)} page records across {df['operator_name'].nunique()} operator(s).\")\n",
    "df[[\"operator_name\", \"page_slug\", \"url\", \"text_length\"]].head(20)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0006",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Word Frequency Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "What are the most frequent content words in each operator's web presence?\n",
    "This gives a first-pass reading of the dominant discursive registers.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Research note:** Pay attention to *what is absent* as much as what is present.\n",
    "Terms like \"planning\", \"objection\", \"community\", \"noise\", \"local\" would suggest\n",
    "territorial embeddedness; their absence constructs the infrastructure as placeless."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0007",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def tokenise(text: str, stopwords_set: set) -> list:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Tokenise text and remove stopwords and short tokens.\"\"\"\n",
    "    if HAVE_NLTK:\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            tokens = word_tokenize(text.lower())\n",
    "            return [t for t in tokens if t.isalpha() and len(t) > 2 and t not in stopwords_set]\n",
    "        except Exception:\n",
    "            pass\n",
    "    # Fallback\n",
    "    tokens = re.findall(r\"[a-z]{3,}\", text.lower())\n",
    "    return [t for t in tokens if t not in stopwords_set]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Build per-operator combined token lists\n",
    "operator_tokens: dict[str, list] = {}\n",
    "for op in df[\"operator_name\"].unique():\n",
    "    combined_text = \" \".join(df[df[\"operator_name\"] == op][\"text\"].tolist())\n",
    "    operator_tokens[op] = tokenise(combined_text, STOPWORDS)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show top-30 words per operator\n",
    "for op, tokens in operator_tokens.items():\n",
    "    top = Counter(tokens).most_common(30)\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n--- {op} (top 30 words) ---\")\n",
    "    for word, count in top:\n",
    "        print(f\"  {word:20s} {count}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0008",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "# Plot: top-20 words per operator as horizontal bar charts\n",
    "# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "n_operators = len(operator_tokens)\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(\n",
    "    1, max(n_operators, 1), figsize=(6 * max(n_operators, 1), 6), sharey=False\n",
    ")\n",
    "if n_operators == 1:\n",
    "    axes = [axes]\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax, (op, tokens) in zip(axes, operator_tokens.items()):\n",
    "    top = Counter(tokens).most_common(20)\n",
    "    words, counts = zip(*top) if top else ([], [])\n",
    "    ax.barh(list(words)[::-1], list(counts)[::-1], color=\"steelblue\")\n",
    "    ax.set_title(op.replace(\"_\", \" \").title(), fontsize=11)\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel(\"Frequency\")\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.suptitle(\"Top-20 Content Words by Operator (Corporate Website)\", fontsize=13, y=1.01)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(REPO_ROOT / \"outputs\" / \"figures\" / \"wp1_word_frequency.png\", bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(\"Saved to outputs/figures/wp1_word_frequency.png\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0009",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Environmental Claim Language Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "We compare keyword density across pre-defined research-relevant categories:\n",
    "`energy`, `water`, `carbon`, `sustainability`, `location`, `community`.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Research question:** Which environmental claims are most prominent? Which are\n",
    "structurally absent? Does operator type (hyperscaler vs. colocation) predict\n",
    "different environmental registers?\n",
    "\n",
    "**Interpretation guide:**\n",
    "- High `sustainability` + low `community` → greenwashing pattern (environmental\n",
    "  claims detached from local territorial impact)\n",
    "- High `energy` + low `location` → efficiency framing that obscures spatial politics\n",
    "- High `carbon` + high `water` → more holistic environmental disclosure"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0010",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Build keyword count matrix from scraped metadata\n",
    "# (keyword_counts were computed by the scraper for each page)\n",
    "kw_categories = [\"energy\", \"water\", \"carbon\", \"location\", \"community\", \"sustainability\"]\n",
    "# NOTE: these match the KEYWORDS_OF_INTEREST dict in scrape_operator_websites.py\n",
    "\n",
    "kw_records = []\n",
    "for _, row in df.iterrows():\n",
    "    kc = row[\"keyword_counts\"]\n",
    "    if not kc:  # meta not available\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "    token_count = max(row[\"text_length\"] // 6, 1)  # rough estimate if tokens not stored\n",
    "    for cat in kw_categories:\n",
    "        count = sum(v for k, v in kc.items() if k in cat or cat in k)\n",
    "        kw_records.append({\n",
    "            \"operator_name\": row[\"operator_name\"],\n",
    "            \"page_slug\": row[\"page_slug\"],\n",
    "            \"category\": cat,\n",
    "            \"count\": count,\n",
    "            \"density_per_1k\": round(count / token_count * 1000, 3),\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "kw_df = pd.DataFrame(kw_records)\n",
    "print(kw_df.head(12))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0011",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Aggregate by operator and category\n",
    "kw_agg = (\n",
    "    kw_df.groupby([\"operator_name\", \"category\"])[\"density_per_1k\"]\n",
    "    .sum()\n",
    "    .reset_index()\n",
    "    .pivot(index=\"operator_name\", columns=\"category\", values=\"density_per_1k\")\n",
    "    .fillna(0)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Heatmap\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, max(3, len(kw_agg) * 0.8 + 1)))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(\n",
    "    kw_agg,\n",
    "    annot=True,\n",
    "    fmt=\".2f\",\n",
    "    cmap=\"YlOrRd\",\n",
    "    linewidths=0.5,\n",
    "    ax=ax,\n",
    "    cbar_kws={\"label\": \"Keyword density (per 1,000 tokens)\"},\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\n",
    "    \"Environmental Claim Keyword Density by Operator\\n(Corporate Website, all pages combined)\",\n",
    "    fontsize=12,\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Keyword category\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Operator\")\n",
    "ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=30, ha=\"right\")\n",
    "ax.set_yticklabels(\n",
    "    [label.get_text().replace(\"_\", \" \").title() for label in ax.get_yticklabels()],\n",
    "    rotation=0,\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(\n",
    "    REPO_ROOT / \"outputs\" / \"figures\" / \"wp1_keyword_heatmap.png\", bbox_inches=\"tight\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(\"Saved to outputs/figures/wp1_keyword_heatmap.png\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0012",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Image Alt Tag Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Image alt tags reflect the *visual register* of operator self-presentation.\n",
    "Operators choose which images to display — and what text to attach to them.\n",
    "Common patterns: nature imagery (\"solar panels\", \"wind turbines\") without\n",
    "specific location; abstract technology imagery (\"servers\", \"connected world\");\n",
    "conspicuously absent: community context, local landscapes, workers.\n",
    "\n",
    "**TODO:** Expand this section with a more systematic coding scheme once\n",
    "sufficient data is collected. Consider a visual analysis framework (e.g.\n",
    "Kress & van Leeuwen's social semiotics of images)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a1b2c3d4-0013",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load image alt texts from metadata files\n",
    "all_alts = []\n",
    "for op_dir in sorted(CORP_DIR.iterdir()):\n",
    "    if not op_dir.is_dir():\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "    for meta_file in op_dir.glob(\"*_meta.json\"):\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            meta = json.loads(meta_file.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n",
    "            for alt in meta.get(\"image_alts\", []):\n",
    "                all_alts.append({\n",
    "                    \"operator\": op_dir.name,\n",
    "                    \"slug\": meta_file.stem.replace(\"_meta\", \"\"),\n",
    "                    \"alt_text\": alt,\n",
    "                })\n",
    "        except Exception:\n",
    "            pass\n",
    "\n",
    "alts_df = pd.DataFrame(all_alts)\n",
    "print(f\"Total image alt tags found: {len(alts_df)}\")\n",
    "alts_df.head(15)"
   ]
  },
